  id: Carpals_L
  partName: Carpals Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - 'The carpals Left consist of multiple small bones that form the wrist joint of
    the forelimb. These bones are arranged in rows and work together to allow flexibility
    and controlled movement. They play an essential role in absorbing shock and distributing
    mechanical forces during locomotion. '
  - By enabling smooth flexion and extension, they support efficient limb motion.
    Proper alignment of the carpal bones ensures stability, reduces strain on surrounding
    tissues, and contributes to overall balance and coordinated forelimb performance.
